{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":0,"text":"Sixty-five million years ago, a very important"},{"time":2000,"text":"and catastrophic event"},{"time":4000,"text":"changed the course of life on land."},{"time":6000,"text":"And although we know that the land animals I'm going to talk about"},{"time":9000,"text":"are just the scum of the Earth on the land --"},{"time":12000,"text":"the little bits of land floating around -- but they are important to us"},{"time":14000,"text":"because they're sort of in our scale of experience from millimeters to meters."},{"time":18000,"text":"And these animals disappeared,"},{"time":21000,"text":"and a separate life, mammals,"},{"time":25000,"text":"radiated out to take their place. And so, we know this"},{"time":27000,"text":"in extraordinary detail. And so this is a core"},{"time":30000,"text":"from near Bermuda. We know that the tsunamis, the earthquakes,"},{"time":33000,"text":"and the things that we've experienced"},{"time":35000,"text":"in the entire record of humankind history"},{"time":37000,"text":"can't really quite get around the kind of disaster"},{"time":40000,"text":"that this represented for the Earth."}]},{"cues":[{"time":44000,"text":"So even before that impact was known,"},{"time":48000,"text":"even before scientists in general came to an agreement"},{"time":51000,"text":"over the theory of evolution,"},{"time":53000,"text":"scientists and natural historians of all kinds of stripes"},{"time":56000,"text":"actually had divided Earth's life's history"},{"time":58000,"text":"into these two episodes:"},{"time":60000,"text":"Mesozoic, the middle life, and the Cenozoic, the recent life."},{"time":64000,"text":"And as it turns out, it actually corresponds really nicely"},{"time":67000,"text":"with geologic history."},{"time":69000,"text":"So we have a Mesozoic period,"},{"time":71000,"text":"an age of fragmentation,"},{"time":73000,"text":"and a Cenozoic period, an age of reconnection --"},{"time":75000,"text":"South America to North America, India to Asia."},{"time":78000,"text":"And so my work, really, is trying to understand"},{"time":81000,"text":"the character of that Mesozoic radiation"},{"time":84000,"text":"compared to the Cenozoic radiation"},{"time":86000,"text":"to see what mysteries we can understand from dinosaurs and from other animals"},{"time":89000,"text":"about what life on drifting continents"},{"time":92000,"text":"really can tell us about evolution."}]},{"cues":[{"time":94000,"text":"The work immediately begs the question,"},{"time":97000,"text":"\"Why didn't they go into the waters?\""},{"time":99000,"text":"I mean, certainly mammals did. This is one example."},{"time":101000,"text":"You can go outside -- see many other examples."},{"time":103000,"text":"Within five, 10 million years of the bolide impact"},{"time":106000,"text":"we had a whole variety of animals going into the water. Why didn't they do that?"},{"time":110000,"text":"Why didn't they hang around in trees at good size,"},{"time":112000,"text":"and why didn't they burrow?"},{"time":114000,"text":"Why didn't they do all these things, and if they didn't do all these things,"},{"time":116000,"text":"what kinds of animals were in those spaces?"},{"time":118000,"text":"And if there were no animals in those spaces, what does that tell us"},{"time":120000,"text":"about, you know, how evolution works on land?"},{"time":124000,"text":"Really interesting questions. I think a lot of it has to do with body size."},{"time":128000,"text":"In fact, I think that most of it has to do with body size --"},{"time":132000,"text":"the size you are when you inherit"},{"time":135000,"text":"a vacant ecospace"},{"time":137000,"text":"from whatever natural disaster."}]},{"cues":[{"time":139000,"text":"Looking at dinosaur evolution"},{"time":141000,"text":"and studying it, digging it up for many years,"},{"time":144000,"text":"I end up looking at the mammal radiation,"},{"time":147000,"text":"and it seems as though everything is quick time, just like technology,"},{"time":150000,"text":"advancing by an order of magnitude."},{"time":152000,"text":"Dinosaur evolution proceeded at a stately pace,"},{"time":155000,"text":"an order of magnitude slower on any way you want to measure it."},{"time":158000,"text":"You want to measure it by diversity?"},{"time":160000,"text":"You want to measure it by"},{"time":162000,"text":"the time it took to reach maximum body size?"},{"time":164000,"text":"Yes, they do have larger body size,"},{"time":166000,"text":"but many of them are smaller,"},{"time":168000,"text":"but we're interested in the time it took them to achieve that."},{"time":170000,"text":"Fifty million years to achieve this maximum body size."},{"time":174000,"text":"And that is 10 times longer than it took the mammals"},{"time":176000,"text":"to achieve maximum body size"},{"time":178000,"text":"and invade all those habitats."}]},{"cues":[{"time":180000,"text":"So there's lessons to learn,"},{"time":182000,"text":"and there's lessons to learn from the exception,"},{"time":185000,"text":"the exception that we know very well today from the discoveries we've made,"},{"time":188000,"text":"and many other scholars have made around the world."},{"time":190000,"text":"This slide was shown before. This is the famous Jurassic bird Archaeopteryx."},{"time":195000,"text":"We now know this transition is the one time"},{"time":197000,"text":"that dinosaurs actually went below"},{"time":199000,"text":"that body size --"},{"time":201000,"text":"we're going to see where they began in a minute --"},{"time":203000,"text":"and it is the one time that they rapidly"},{"time":205000,"text":"invaded all the habitats"},{"time":207000,"text":"I just told you that dinosaurs weren't in."},{"time":209000,"text":"They became marine. We now know them today"},{"time":211000,"text":"from the ice caps."},{"time":213000,"text":"There's burrowing birds."},{"time":215000,"text":"They inhabit the trees at all body sizes,"},{"time":217000,"text":"and, of course, they inhabit the land."}]},{"cues":[{"time":219000,"text":"So we were the first to actually name a bird from the famous series"},{"time":223000,"text":"that later exploded onto the pages of Science and Nature."},{"time":227000,"text":"We called this bird Sinornis. It's a little bit more advanced than Archaeopteryx,"},{"time":230000,"text":"and if you go to different layers, you find things"},{"time":232000,"text":"that are less advanced than Archaeopteryx, and every grade in between,\n\n"},{"time":235000,"text":"so that if you find something today, we're usually splitting hairs --"},{"time":239000,"text":"or, more appropriately, feathers -- as to decide whether it's actually"},{"time":241000,"text":"a non-avian or an avian."},{"time":243000,"text":"It is the greatest transition that we have, actually,"},{"time":245000,"text":"on land from one habitat to another,"},{"time":247000,"text":"bar none,"},{"time":249000,"text":"to understand how a bony,"},{"time":251000,"text":"fairly heavy, kilogram or a couple-of-kilogram animal"},{"time":254000,"text":"could make such a transition."},{"time":256000,"text":"It is really our greatest -- one of our greatest -- evolutionary sequences."}]},{"cues":[{"time":259000,"text":"Now, my work began at the beginning."},{"time":261000,"text":"I thought if I'm going to understand dinosaur evolution,"},{"time":263000,"text":"I'd have to go back to those beds"},{"time":265000,"text":"where they had picked up fragments, go back to a time and a place"},{"time":268000,"text":"where the earliest dinosaurs existed."},{"time":270000,"text":"I'd like to call for this little video clip"},{"time":273000,"text":"to give you some idea of, sort of, what we face. Normally, we get asked a lot of questions:"},{"time":276000,"text":"\"Well, how do you find fossils in areas that look like this?\""},{"time":280000,"text":"If we could roll that first video clip."},{"time":283000,"text":"This is sort of a nice helicopter ride"},{"time":285000,"text":"through those early beds,"},{"time":287000,"text":"and they're located in Northeastern Argentina."},{"time":289000,"text":"And we're coming over a cliff, and at the top of that cliff,"},{"time":292000,"text":"dinosaurs had basically taken over."},{"time":294000,"text":"At the bottom of the cliff, we find that they're rare as hens' teeth."},{"time":297000,"text":"That's where dinosaur origins is to be found: at the bottom of the cliff."}]},{"cues":[{"time":300000,"text":"You go into an area like this, you get a geologic map,"},{"time":301000,"text":"you get a topographic map,"},{"time":303000,"text":"and the best, most-inspired team you can bring to the area."},{"time":307000,"text":"And the rest is up to you. You've got to find fossils."},{"time":310000,"text":"You've got to dig a hole that's usually quite a bit bigger than that"},{"time":313000,"text":"to get it out; you've got to climb those cliffs"},{"time":315000,"text":"and find, really, everything that existed --"},{"time":319000,"text":"not just the dinosaurs, but the entire story. If you're lucky,"},{"time":321000,"text":"and you dig a place like that,"},{"time":323000,"text":"you actually find the ash bed to dig it, and we did."},{"time":326000,"text":"228 million years old, we found"},{"time":330000,"text":"what really is the most primitive dinosaur:"},{"time":332000,"text":"that's the Ur-dinosaur."},{"time":334000,"text":"A three-and-a-half foot thing,"},{"time":336000,"text":"beautiful skull, predator,"},{"time":338000,"text":"meat-eater, a two-legged animal."},{"time":340000,"text":"So, all the other dinosaurs that you know,"},{"time":342000,"text":"or your kids know, at least, on four legs."},{"time":344000,"text":"This is sort of a look at the skull,"},{"time":346000,"text":"and it's an absolutely fantastic thing about five or six inches long."},{"time":349000,"text":"It looks rather bird-like because it is."},{"time":352000,"text":"It's bird-like and hollow."},{"time":354000,"text":"A predator. Maybe 25 pounds,"},{"time":356000,"text":"or 10 kilograms."},{"time":358000,"text":"That's where dinosaurs began. That's where the radiation began."},{"time":360000,"text":"That is 10 times larger"},{"time":362000,"text":"than the mammal radiation, which was a four-legged radiation."},{"time":365000,"text":"We are extremely dinosaur-like,"},{"time":367000,"text":"and unusual in our two-legged approach to life."}]},{"cues":[{"time":371000,"text":"Now, if you want to understand what happened"},{"time":373000,"text":"then when the continents broke apart,"},{"time":375000,"text":"and dinosaurs found -- landlubbers, as they are --"},{"time":377000,"text":"found themselves adrift. There's some missing puzzle pieces."},{"time":383000,"text":"Most of those missing puzzle pieces are southern continents,"},{"time":384000,"text":"because it was those continents that are least explored."},{"time":387000,"text":"If you want to add to this picture and try and sketch it globally,"},{"time":390000,"text":"you really have to force yourself to go down"},{"time":392000,"text":"to the four corners of the Earth --"},{"time":394000,"text":"Africa, India, Antarctica, Australia --"},{"time":397000,"text":"and start putting together some of these pieces."},{"time":400000,"text":"I've been to some of those continents, but Africa was,"},{"time":403000,"text":"in the words of Steven Pinker, was a blank slate, largely."},{"time":406000,"text":"But one with an immense chalkboard in the middle,"},{"time":409000,"text":"with lots of little areas of dinosaur rock"},{"time":411000,"text":"if you could survive an expedition."}]},{"cues":[{"time":414000,"text":"There's no roads into the Sahara. It's an enormous place."},{"time":417000,"text":"To be able to excavate"},{"time":419000,"text":"the 80 tons of dinosaurs that we have in the Sahara"},{"time":422000,"text":"and take them out, you really have to put together"},{"time":425000,"text":"an expedition team that can handle the conditions."},{"time":428000,"text":"Some of them are political. Many of them are physical.\n\n"},{"time":431000,"text":"Some of them -- the most important -- are mental. \n\n"},{"time":434000,"text":"And you really have to be able to withstand conditions --"},{"time":436000,"text":"you have to drive into the desert,"},{"time":438000,"text":"you will see landscapes in many cases --"},{"time":441000,"text":"you can see from what we've discovered --"},{"time":442000,"text":"that nobody else has ever seen."},{"time":444000,"text":"And the kinds of teams they bring in?"},{"time":446000,"text":"Well, they're"},{"time":450000,"text":"composed of"},{"time":452000,"text":"people who understand science as adventure with a purpose."},{"time":455000,"text":"They're usually students who've never seen a desert."},{"time":457000,"text":"Some of them are more experienced."}]},{"cues":[{"time":459000,"text":"Your job as a leader -- this is definitely a team sport --"},{"time":461000,"text":"your job as a leader is to try to inspire them"},{"time":464000,"text":"to do more work than they've ever done in their life"},{"time":466000,"text":"under conditions that they can't imagine."},{"time":469000,"text":"So, 125 degrees is normal."},{"time":471000,"text":"The ground surface at 150 -- typical."},{"time":475000,"text":"So, you can't leave your normal metal tools out"},{"time":478000,"text":"because you'll get a first-degree burn if you grab them sometimes."},{"time":481000,"text":"So, you are finding yourself also in an amazing cultural milieu."},{"time":485000,"text":"You're really rubbing shoulders"},{"time":487000,"text":"with the world's last great nomadic people."},{"time":491000,"text":"These are the Tuareg nomads, and they're living their lives"},{"time":493000,"text":"much as they have for centuries."},{"time":496000,"text":"Your job is to excavate things like this in the foreground,"},{"time":498000,"text":"and make them enter the pages of history."},{"time":500000,"text":"To do that, you've got to actually transport them"},{"time":502000,"text":"thousands of miles out of the desert."}]},{"cues":[{"time":504000,"text":"We're talking about Ethiopia, but let's talk about Niger --"},{"time":506000,"text":"or Niger, in our English language -- north of Nigeria --"},{"time":509000,"text":"that's where this photograph was taken."},{"time":511000,"text":"Basically you're talking about a country that,"},{"time":513000,"text":"when we started working there, did not have container traffic."},{"time":517000,"text":"You transported the bones out yourself"},{"time":519000,"text":"to the coast of Africa,"},{"time":522000,"text":"onto a boat, if you wanted to get them out of the middle of the Sahara."},{"time":524000,"text":"That's a 2,000 mile journey."},{"time":526000,"text":"So enormous excavations and a lot of work,"},{"time":530000,"text":"and out of essentially a partial herd of dinosaurs"},{"time":532000,"text":"that you saw buried there -- 20 tons of material --"},{"time":536000,"text":"we erect Jobaria,"},{"time":538000,"text":"a sauropod dinosaur like we haven't seen on some other continents."},{"time":540000,"text":"It really is a little bit out of place temporally."},{"time":542000,"text":"It looks nothing like what we would find"},{"time":544000,"text":"if we dug in contemporary beds in North America."},{"time":547000,"text":"Here's the animal that was causing it trouble."}]},{"cues":[{"time":551000,"text":"And, you know, on and on --"},{"time":553000,"text":"a whole menagerie. When you pick up something like this --"},{"time":555000,"text":"and some of you have had the chance to touch it --"},{"time":557000,"text":"this is a piece of history. You're touching something that's 110 million years old."},{"time":559000,"text":"This is a thumb claw. There it was, moments after it was discovered."},{"time":562000,"text":"It is an incredible view of life,"},{"time":564000,"text":"and it really began when we began to understand"},{"time":566000,"text":"the depth of time."},{"time":568000,"text":"It's only been with us for less than a century,"},{"time":570000,"text":"and in that time, that fourth dimension,"},{"time":572000,"text":"when radioactive dating came about, less than a century ago,"},{"time":575000,"text":"and we could actually tell how old some of these things were,"},{"time":579000,"text":"is probably the most profound transformation,"},{"time":581000,"text":"because it changes the way we look at ourselves"},{"time":583000,"text":"and the world dramatically."},{"time":585000,"text":"When you pick up a piece of history like that,"},{"time":587000,"text":"I think it can transform"},{"time":589000,"text":"kids that are possibly interested in science."}]},{"cues":[{"time":591000,"text":"That's the animal that thumb claw came from: Suchomimus."},{"time":594000,"text":"Here's some others."},{"time":596000,"text":"This is something we found in Morocco, an immense animal."},{"time":599000,"text":"We prototyped by CAT-scanning the brain out of this animal."},{"time":602000,"text":"It turns out to have a forebrain"},{"time":604000,"text":"one-fifteenth the size of a human."},{"time":607000,"text":"This was the cover of Science, because they thought"},{"time":609000,"text":"that humans were more intelligent than these animals, \n\n"},{"time":611000,"text":"but we can see by some in our administration"},{"time":613000,"text":"that despite"},{"time":616000,"text":"the enormous advantage in brain volume"},{"time":618000,"text":"some of the attitudes remain the same. Anyway,"},{"time":622000,"text":"smaller raptors."},{"time":625000,"text":"All the stuff from Jurassic Park that you know of --"},{"time":627000,"text":"all those small animals --"},{"time":629000,"text":"they all come from northern continents."},{"time":631000,"text":"This is the first skeleton from a southern continent,"},{"time":633000,"text":"and guess what? You start preparing it."},{"time":636000,"text":"It has no big claw on its hind foot. It doesn't look like a Velociraptor."},{"time":639000,"text":"It's really a wholly separate radiation."},{"time":641000,"text":"So what we're trying to piece together here is a story."},{"time":643000,"text":"It involves flying reptiles like this Pterosaur"},{"time":646000,"text":"that we reconstructed from Africa."}]},{"cues":[{"time":648000,"text":"Crocodiles, of course,"},{"time":650000,"text":"and that's a nasty one we haven't named yet."},{"time":653000,"text":"And huge things -- I mean, this is a"},{"time":656000,"text":"lower jaw just laying there in the desert"},{"time":658000,"text":"of this enormous crocodile."},{"time":660000,"text":"The crocodile is technically called Sarcosuchus."},{"time":663000,"text":"That's an adult Orinoco crocodile in its jaws."},{"time":666000,"text":"We had to try and reconstruct this."},{"time":668000,"text":"We had to actually look at recent crocodiles"},{"time":670000,"text":"to understand how crocodiles scale."},{"time":673000,"text":"Could I have the second little video clip?"},{"time":675000,"text":"Now, this field is just -- and, of course, science in general -- is just -- adventure."},{"time":681000,"text":"We had to find and measure"},{"time":683000,"text":"the largest crocodiles living today."}]},{"cues":[{"time":685000,"text":"Narrator: ... as long as their boat."}]},{"cues":[{"time":687000,"text":"Man: Look at that set of choppers! Yeah, he's a big one."}]},{"cues":[{"time":690000,"text":"Narrator: If they can just land it,"},{"time":692000,"text":"this croc will provide useful data,"},{"time":694000,"text":"helping Paul in his quest to understand Sarcosuchus."}]},{"cues":[{"time":698000,"text":"Man: OK, hand me some more here. Man 2: OK."}]},{"cues":[{"time":702000,"text":"Narrator: It falls to Paul to cover its eyes."}]},{"cues":[{"time":708000,"text":"Man: Watch out! Watch out! No, no, no, no. You're going to have to get on the back legs."}]},{"cues":[{"time":712000,"text":"Man: I got the back legs."}]},{"cues":[{"time":714000,"text":"Man 2: You have the back legs? No, you have the front legs, my friend."},{"time":716000,"text":"I've got it. I've got the back legs."},{"time":719000,"text":"Somebody get the front legs."}]},{"cues":[{"time":726000,"text":"Paul Sereno: Let's get this tape measure on him. Put it right there."},{"time":731000,"text":"Wow."},{"time":733000,"text":"Sixty-five. Wow."},{"time":736000,"text":"That's a big skull."}]},{"cues":[{"time":738000,"text":"Narrator: Big, but less than half the size"},{"time":740000,"text":"of supercroc's skull."}]},{"cues":[{"time":742000,"text":"Man: Enormous. PS: You've got a ... 14-foot croc."}]},{"cues":[{"time":746000,"text":"Man: I knew it was big."}]},{"cues":[{"time":751000,"text":"PS: Don't get off. You don't get off, but don't worry about me."}]},{"cues":[{"time":755000,"text":"Narrator: Paul has his data, so they decide"},{"time":757000,"text":"to release the animal back into the river."}]},{"cues":[{"time":764000,"text":"PS: Don't get off! Don't get off! Don't get off!"}]},{"cues":[{"time":769000,"text":"Narrator: Paul has never seen a fossil do that."}]},{"cues":[{"time":773000,"text":"PS: Okay, when I say three, we move."},{"time":775000,"text":"One, two, three!"},{"time":780000,"text":"Whoa!"}]},{"cues":[{"time":782000,"text":"So -- there were --"},{"time":785000,"text":"(Applause)"},{"time":790000,"text":"Well, you know, the -- the fossil record is truly amazing"},{"time":793000,"text":"because it really forces you to look at living animals in a new way."},{"time":795000,"text":"We proved with those measurements"},{"time":797000,"text":"that crocodiles scaled isometrically."},{"time":800000,"text":"It depended on the shape of their skull, though,"},{"time":801000,"text":"so we had to actually get those measurements"},{"time":803000,"text":"to be sure that we had reconstructed and could prove to the scientific world"},{"time":806000,"text":"that supercroc in fact is a 40-foot crocodile, probably a male."},{"time":809000,"text":"Anyway, you find other things, too."},{"time":811000,"text":"I'm going to lead an expedition to the Sahara"},{"time":813000,"text":"to dig up Africa's largest neolithic site."},{"time":817000,"text":"We found this last year."},{"time":819000,"text":"Two hundred skeletons, tools, jewelry."}]},{"cues":[{"time":821000,"text":"This is a ceremonial disk."},{"time":824000,"text":"An amazing record of the colonization of the Sahara"},{"time":827000,"text":"5,000 years ago is been sitting out there"},{"time":829000,"text":"waiting for us to go back. So, really exciting."},{"time":831000,"text":"And then work later is going to take us to Tibet."},{"time":834000,"text":"Now, we normally think of Tibet as a highland."},{"time":836000,"text":"It's really an island continent."},{"time":838000,"text":"It was a precursor to India,"},{"time":840000,"text":"a messenger from Gondwana --"},{"time":843000,"text":"a lost paradise of dinosaurs \n\n"},{"time":845000,"text":"isolated for millions of years."},{"time":847000,"text":"No one's found them. We know where they are,"},{"time":849000,"text":"and we're going to go and get them next year."},{"time":851000,"text":"They're only between 13 and 14,000 feet,"},{"time":854000,"text":"but if you go in the warm part of the year, it's O.K."},{"time":857000,"text":"Now, I tried to suture together a dinosaur evolutionary history"},{"time":860000,"text":"so that we can try to understand"},{"time":862000,"text":"some basic patterns of evolution."},{"time":864000,"text":"I've talked about a few of them. We really need to take that further."},{"time":867000,"text":"We need to delve into this mass of anatomy"},{"time":869000,"text":"that we've been compiling"},{"time":871000,"text":"to understand where the changes are occurring and what this means."},{"time":874000,"text":"We can't predict, necessarily, what will happen in evolution,"},{"time":876000,"text":"but we can learn some of the rules of the game,"},{"time":878000,"text":"and that's really what we're trying to do."}]},{"cues":[{"time":880000,"text":"With regard to the biogeographic question,"},{"time":882000,"text":"the Earth is dividing."},{"time":884000,"text":"These are all landlubbing animals. There's a couple of choices."},{"time":886000,"text":"You get divided, and a continent's division"},{"time":889000,"text":"corresponds to a fork in the evolutionary tree,"},{"time":891000,"text":"or you're crafty, and you manage to escape"},{"time":894000,"text":"from one to the other and erase that division,"},{"time":897000,"text":"or you're living peacefully on each side,"},{"time":900000,"text":"and on one side you just go extinct,"},{"time":902000,"text":"and you survive on the other side and create a difference."},{"time":905000,"text":"And the fourth thing is that you actually did one or the other"},{"time":907000,"text":"of those three things, but the paleontologist never found you."},{"time":910000,"text":"And you take those four instances"},{"time":913000,"text":"and you realize you have a complex problem."},{"time":916000,"text":"And so, in addition to digging, I think we have some answers"},{"time":919000,"text":"from the dinosaur record. I think these dinosaurs migrated --"},{"time":922000,"text":"we call it dispersal -- around the globe, with the slightest land bridge."},{"time":925000,"text":"They did it within two or three degrees of the pole,"},{"time":929000,"text":"to maintain similarity between continents."},{"time":931000,"text":"But when they were divided, indeed they were divided,"},{"time":934000,"text":"and we do see the continents"},{"time":936000,"text":"carving differences among dinosaurs."}]},{"cues":[{"time":938000,"text":"But there's one thing that's even more important, and I think that's extinction."},{"time":941000,"text":"We have downgraded this factor."},{"time":943000,"text":"It carves up the history of life,"},{"time":945000,"text":"and gives us the differences that we see"},{"time":947000,"text":"in the dinosaur world towards the end,"},{"time":949000,"text":"right before the bolide impact."},{"time":951000,"text":"The best way to test this is to actually create a model."},{"time":953000,"text":"So if we move back, this is a two-dimensional typical tree of life."},{"time":957000,"text":"I want to give you three dimensions."},{"time":959000,"text":"So you see the tree of life,"},{"time":962000,"text":"but now I've added the dimension of area."},{"time":965000,"text":"So the tree of life is normally divergence over time.\n"},{"time":969000,"text":"Now we have divergence over time, but we've created the third dimension of area."}]},{"cues":[{"time":972000,"text":"This is a computer program"},{"time":974000,"text":"which has three knobs."},{"time":976000,"text":"We can control those things that we're worried about:"},{"time":978000,"text":"extinction, sampling, dispersal --"},{"time":982000,"text":"going from one area to another."},{"time":984000,"text":"And ultimately we can control the branching"},{"time":986000,"text":"to mimic what we think the continents were like,"},{"time":989000,"text":"and run it a thousand times, so we can estimate the parameters,"},{"time":993000,"text":"to answer the question whether we are on the mark or not,"},{"time":996000,"text":"at least to know the barriers of the problems. So that's a little bit about the science."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1000000,"text":"Today I'm going to spend the rest of my few minutes up here"},{"time":1001000,"text":"talking about the other stuff that I do in Chicago,"},{"time":1005000,"text":"which is related to the fact that I never --"},{"time":1007000,"text":"and actually, in talking to a lot of TEDsters,"},{"time":1010000,"text":"there's a number of you out there -- I don't know that I'd get an answer"},{"time":1013000,"text":"honestly, if I asked you to raise your hand,"},{"time":1015000,"text":"but there are a number of you out there that started your"},{"time":1017000,"text":"scientific, technical, entertainment career"},{"time":1020000,"text":"as failures, by society's standards, as failures by schools."},{"time":1024000,"text":"I was one of those. I was failed by my school -- my school failed me."},{"time":1027000,"text":"Who's pointing fingers?"},{"time":1029000,"text":"Several teachers nearly killed me."},{"time":1032000,"text":"I found myself in art."},{"time":1034000,"text":"I was a total failure in school, not really headed to graduate high school."},{"time":1037000,"text":"And I went on -- that's my first painting on canvas."},{"time":1039000,"text":"I read a dictionary. I got into college."},{"time":1041000,"text":"I became an artist. O.K., and started drawing."},{"time":1043000,"text":"It became abstract."},{"time":1045000,"text":"I worked up a portfolio, and I was headed to New York."},{"time":1047000,"text":"Sometimes I would see bones when there was a body there."},{"time":1050000,"text":"Something was going on in the background. I headed to New York to a studio."},{"time":1054000,"text":"I took a side trip to the American Museum, and I never recovered."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1058000,"text":"But really it's the same discipline -- they're kindred disciplines."},{"time":1061000,"text":"I mean, is there anything"},{"time":1063000,"text":"that is not visualizing what can't be seen,"},{"time":1066000,"text":"in terms of discovering this dinosaur bone from a small piece of it"},{"time":1069000,"text":"that's out there, or seeing the distortion"},{"time":1071000,"text":"that we try to see"},{"time":1073000,"text":"as evolutionary distortion in one animal to another?"},{"time":1075000,"text":"This is a very extraordinarily visual."},{"time":1077000,"text":"I give you a human face because you're experts at that."},{"time":1079000,"text":"It takes us years to understand how to do that with dinosaurs."},{"time":1083000,"text":"They're really kindred disciplines."},{"time":1085000,"text":"But what we're trying to create in Chicago"},{"time":1088000,"text":"is a way to get,"},{"time":1091000,"text":"collect together, those students"},{"time":1093000,"text":"who are least represented in our science and technology spheres."},{"time":1096000,"text":"We all know, and there's been several allusions to it,"},{"time":1099000,"text":"that we are failing in our ability to produce"},{"time":1102000,"text":"enough scientists, engineers and technicians."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1105000,"text":"We've known that for a long time. We've gone through the Sputnik phase,"},{"time":1108000,"text":"and now, as you see the increase"},{"time":1110000,"text":"in the pace of what we're doing,"},{"time":1112000,"text":"it becomes even more prominent. \nWhere are all these people going to come from?"},{"time":1115000,"text":"And a more general question for our society is,"},{"time":1117000,"text":"what's going to happen to all the rest that are left behind?"},{"time":1120000,"text":"What about all the kids like me that were in school --"},{"time":1122000,"text":"kids like some of you out there --"},{"time":1124000,"text":"that were in school and didn't get a chance and will never get a chance"},{"time":1127000,"text":"to participate in science and technology?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":1129000,"text":"Those are the questions I ask. And we talk about Ethiopia, and it's very important."},{"time":1132000,"text":"Niger is equally important, and I'm trying desperately"},{"time":1134000,"text":"to do something in Niger."},{"time":1136000,"text":"They have an AIDS problem. I asked --"},{"time":1138000,"text":"the U.S. State Department asked the government recently,"},{"time":1141000,"text":"What do you want to do? And they gave them two problems."},{"time":1143000,"text":"Dinosaurs was one of them."},{"time":1145000,"text":"Give us a museum of dinosaurs,"},{"time":1147000,"text":"and we will attract tourists, which is our number two industry."},{"time":1150000,"text":"And I hope to God the United States government, me, or TED,"},{"time":1154000,"text":"or somebody helps us do that, because that would be an incredible thing for their country."},{"time":1157000,"text":"But when we look back at our own country, we're looking back at our cities,"},{"time":1160000,"text":"the cities where most of you come from -- certainly the city I come from --"},{"time":1162000,"text":"there's legions of kids out there"},{"time":1164000,"text":"like these."},{"time":1166000,"text":"And the question is -- and we started to address this question for centuries --"},{"time":1169000,"text":"as to how we get these kids involved in science."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1172000,"text":"We've started in Chicago"},{"time":1174000,"text":"an organization -- a non-profit organization --"},{"time":1176000,"text":"called Project Exploration."},{"time":1178000,"text":"These are two kids from Project Exploration."},{"time":1180000,"text":"We met them in their early stages in high school. They were --"},{"time":1182000,"text":"failing to poor students,"},{"time":1184000,"text":"and they are now -- one at the University of Chicago, another in Illinois."},{"time":1188000,"text":"We've got students at Harvard. We're six years old."},{"time":1190000,"text":"And we created a track record."},{"time":1192000,"text":"Because when you go out there as a scholar, and you try to find out longitudinal studies,"},{"time":1195000,"text":"track records like that, there essentially are very few, if none."},{"time":1199000,"text":"So, we've created an incredible track record of 100 percent graduation,"},{"time":1203000,"text":"90 percent going to college, many first-generation,"},{"time":1206000,"text":"90 percent of those choosing science as a career."},{"time":1209000,"text":"It's an impressive track record, and so we look back and we say,"},{"time":1212000,"text":"well, we didn't really exactly work this out theoretically from the start,"},{"time":1215000,"text":"but when we look back, there are theoretical movements in science education."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1218000,"text":"It's gone through science as an inquiry,"},{"time":1220000,"text":"which was a big advance,"},{"time":1223000,"text":"and Dewey back at Chicago --"},{"time":1225000,"text":"you learn by doing."},{"time":1227000,"text":"To -- you learn by envisioning yourself"},{"time":1232000,"text":"as a scientist,"},{"time":1234000,"text":"and then you learn to envision yourself as a scientist."},{"time":1237000,"text":"The next step is to learn the capability"},{"time":1239000,"text":"to make yourself a scientist."},{"time":1242000,"text":"You have to have those steps. If you have --"},{"time":1244000,"text":"It's easy to get kids interested in science."},{"time":1246000,"text":"It's hard to get them to envision themselves as a scientist,"},{"time":1249000,"text":"which involves standing up in front of people like we're doing here at this symposium"},{"time":1253000,"text":"and presenting something as a knowledgeable person,"},{"time":1255000,"text":"and then seeing yourself in the role as a scientist"},{"time":1258000,"text":"and giving yourself the tools to pursue that."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1261000,"text":"And so, that's what we're going to do. We're planning a permanent home in Chicago."},{"time":1264000,"text":"We have lots of ideas, but I guarantee you this one thing --"},{"time":1266000,"text":"and I've talked to some people here at TED --"},{"time":1268000,"text":"it's not going to look like anything you've seen before."},{"time":1270000,"text":"It's going to be part-school, part-museum hall,"},{"time":1272000,"text":"part-conservatory, part-zoo,"},{"time":1275000,"text":"and part of an answer to the problem"},{"time":1278000,"text":"of how you interest kids in science."},{"time":1279000,"text":"Thank you very much."}]}]}